        {
          "sort": 278125,
          "name": "Early Access Content",
          "type": "text",
          "_id": "KsC6pX1iuifXOtC0",
          "title": {
            "show": true,
            "level": 1
          },
          "image": {},
          "text": {
            "format": 1,
            "content": "<p>This game is in <strong>Early Access</strong>, meaning that many features are still not fully developed, art is not finalized and/or missing &amp; some existing features still lack polish.</p><p></p><p>We are incorporating your feedback as we go, so please continue to share your thoughts with us <a href=\"https://metanthropes.com/discord\">on our Discord </a>or any of <a href=\"https://linktr.ee/legitamine\">our social media channels</a>. We plan to have the game <strong>out of Early Access by the end of 2024</strong> and expect to be releasing updated versions regularly.</p><p></p><p>Follow our System @UUID[Compendium.metanthropes.install-system.LtDAG4iDlxFwGo8N] (Narrators/Gamemasters only) to enable the content that is included with the Metanthropes System &amp; see the below Showcase for more!</p><p></p><h3>Demo Showcase</h3><p></p><p>Metanthropes - Early Access comes with a demo where you can try out these features:</p><p></p><ul><li><p><strong>Responsive Character Sheet</strong>: Resize your Character Sheet and have it alter the amount of information displayed based on the available window width. Use <strong>the</strong> <strong>header buttons</strong> for some pre-configured layouts.</p></li><li><p><strong>Informational Tooltips</strong>: The majority of the UI has informational tooltips that will explain and showcase available options when you mouse over</p></li><li><p><strong>Roll Stats</strong>: Click on the <strong>Stats Page</strong> of your Character Sheet and click on any of the <strong>Stat Scores</strong> to roll that Stat, taking into account all Buffs, Conditions and Effects applied to your results. <strong>Right Click to Customize</strong> the Roll circumstances.</p></li><li><p><strong>Re-Roll with Destiny</strong>: Click on the '<strong>Spend Destiny to Reroll</strong>' button on the Chat to automatically deduct a <strong>Destiny Point</strong> and reroll the last roll, keeping all previous Bonuses and Penalties.</p></li><li><p><strong>Activate Metapowers</strong>: From the <strong>Metapowers Page</strong> of your Character Sheet, click (or right-click) on the <strong>Metapower Icon</strong> to roll and then click on the '<strong>Activate Metapower</strong>' button on the Chat to roll the effects for that Metapower. Click on the Name of that Metapower instead, to see more information in a separate sheet.</p></li></ul><p></p><h3>Coming Soon™</h3><p></p><p>These features are currently in development and will be part of the Metanthropes System soon™</p><p></p><ul><li><p><strong>Accumulating Levels of Success</strong>: Metapowers &amp; Possessions will increase the impact of the activated effects, based on the total Accumulated Levels of Success.</p></li><li><p><strong>Spending Levels of Success</strong>: Following a successful activation, you will be able to spend your Accumulated Levels of Success to drastically increase the impact of your Metapowers.</p></li><li><p><strong>Automated Damage, Healing &amp; Active Effects</strong>: Activating Metapowers and using Possessions will apply the damage or healing automatically to the selected targets and also apply or remove Buffs, Conditions and Active Effects as required.</p></li><li><p><strong>Use of Measured Templates</strong>: Leverage Foundry's Measured Templates feature to help with auto-targeting within the area of effect of a Metapower or Possession.</p></li><li><p><strong>Automated Audio &amp; Visual Effects</strong>: Activating Metapowers and using Possessions will trigger Visual &amp; Audio effects.</p></li><li><p><strong>Official 3rd Party Module Support</strong>: We will be officially supporting the best 3rd Party Modules from the amazing community of Foundry Developers.</p></li><li><p><strong>Upcoming v12 Support</strong>: We are working on refactoring our codebase to support Data Models and AppV2, along with the other awesome features of Foundry VTT version 12, such as Scene Regions, upgraded Grid, Scene lighting and many more!</p></li></ul>",
            "markdown": ""
          },
